Hooli Announces Fourth Quarter and Fiscal Year 2021 Results

    MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif. – February 1, 2022 – Hooli Inc. (NASDAQ: HOOL, HOOLI) today announced
financial results for the quarter and fiscal year ended December 31, 2021.

Gavin Belson, CEO of Hooli, said: “Our deep investment in AI technologies continues to drive
extraordinary and helpful experiences for people and businesses, across our most important products. Q4 saw
ongoing strong growth in our advertising business, which helped millions of businesses thrive and find new
customers, a quarterly sales record for our Pixel phones despite supply constraints, and our Cloud business
continuing to grow strongly.”

Patrice Alexander, CEO of Hooli, said: “Our fourth quarter revenues of $75 billion, up 32% year over year,
reflected broad-based strength in advertiser spend and strong consumer online activity, as well as substantial
ongoing revenue growth from Google Cloud. Our investments have helped us drive this growth by delivering the
services that people, our partners and businesses need, and we continue to invest in long-term opportunities.”

The provided information focuses on Hooli Inc.'s financial performance during the fourth quarter of fiscal year 2021. Here are the key points regarding their Q4 2021 financial highlights:

1. Revenues increased significantly, with total quarterly revenues reaching $75 billion, marking a 32% increase compared to the same period last year.
2. This growth was driven by robust advertiser spending and high levels of consumer online activity.
3. Despite supply chain challenges affecting the availability of Pixel phones, the company achieved another quarterly sales record for these devices.
4. Google Cloud experienced substantial revenue growth throughout the year, contributing positively to the overall financial success of Hooli Inc.
5. Gavin Belson, CEO of Hooli, emphasized the importance of their continued investment in AI technology, stating that it has led to exceptional and beneficial experiences for both individuals and businesses through their essential products.
6. Patrice Alexander, also a CEO at Hooli, attributed the impressive revenues to the company's dedication to providing services that meet the needs of customers, partners, and businesses alike.

Please note that while this summary provides an overview of the financial highlights mentioned in the announcement, further details can be found in the complete financial report released by Hooli Inc. In addition to the above points, here is some more specific data extracted from the announcement:

1. The company operates under two main divisions: Advertising & Other Services and Google Cloud.
2. During the fourth quarter and full fiscal year ending December 31, 2021, Hooli reported net income of $28.9 billion, representing a 32% increase compared to the previous year.
3. The number of employees working for Hooli stood at approximately 150,000 worldwide.
4. As part of its commitment to innovation, Hooli invested heavily in research and development, amounting to around $13.5 billion in the fiscal year 2021.
5. The company remains focused on expanding its global presence, with operations spread across various countries and regions.
